<rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><language>en</language><title>The France 24 Observers - Breaking the news thanks to amateur images - Film, verify, share.</title><description>The France 24 Observers is both a website and a TV show focusing on international news through the lens of amateur images. Our journalists analyze and verify all contents, spot and expose fake news from around the world.</description><link>https://observers.france24.com/en/</link><lastBuildDate>Fri, 06 Mar 2026 01:37:17 GMT</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://observers.france24.com/en/rss" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><category></category><title>The Observers are moving to the FRANCE 24 website</title><link>https://observers.france24.com/en/the-observers-are-moving-to-the-france-24-website</link><description></description><media:thumbnail url="https://s.observers.france24.com/media/display/15d907f4-8980-11f0-969d-005056bf30b7/w:1024/p:16x9/img-default-OBS-1.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://s.observers.france24.com/media/display/15d907f4-8980-11f0-969d-005056bf30b7/w:1024/p:16x9/img-default-OBS-1.jpg" type="image/jpeg" length="0"/><guid isPermaLink="false">def4cc00-897f-11f0-9ed2-f1ed2f81d806</guid><pubDate>Thu, 04 Sep 2025 11:13:13 GMT</pubDate><source url="https://s.observers.france24.com/media/display/15d907f4-8980-11f0-969d-005056bf30b7/w:1024/p:16x9/img-default-OBS-1.jpg">© Observers</source><dc:creator>Observers team</dc:creator></item><item><category></category><title>How Russia is building airports to launch Iranian drones at Ukraine</title><link>https://www.france24.com/en/europe/20250827-russia-building-airports-launch-iranian-drones-shahed-ukraine</link><description>
The number of Russian strikes on Ukraine using Shahed kamikaze drones has been rising significantly since the beginning of the year, terrorising civilians. In order to continue its relentless drone campaign, Russia has been setting up special airports custom-built for mass drone launches. The FRANCE 24 Observers team used satellite images to pinpoint these sites.
</description><media:thumbnail url="https://s.observers.france24.com/media/display/9cb58854-8374-11f0-91cb-005056bfb2b6/w:1024/p:16x9/image1-118.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://s.observers.france24.com/media/display/9cb58854-8374-11f0-91cb-005056bfb2b6/w:1024/p:16x9/image1-118.jpg" type="image/jpeg" length="0"/><guid isPermaLink="false">a9d72ef2-8374-11f0-8e77-cb903fe5ead7</guid><pubDate>Wed, 27 Aug 2025 18:35:53 GMT</pubDate></item><item><category></category><title>Famine in Gaza: ‘It’s not just a humanitarian crisis, it's a daily tragedy’</title><link>https://www.france24.com/en/middle-east/20250826-famine-gaza-city-humanitarian-crisis-daily-tragedy</link><description>
For the first time since the war in Gaza began in October 2023, the UN declared a famine in the Gaza governorate on August 22. The FRANCE 24 Observers team spoke to several local food distribution organisations who say the declaration “comes too late”, as part of the population “has been starving for months”.
</description><media:thumbnail url="https://s.observers.france24.com/media/display/b5140d34-8294-11f0-96af-005056a97e36/w:1024/p:16x9/Design-sans-titre-48.png"/><enclosure url="https://s.observers.france24.com/media/display/b5140d34-8294-11f0-96af-005056a97e36/w:1024/p:16x9/Design-sans-titre-48.png" type="image/png" length="0"/><guid isPermaLink="false">3f78affc-8295-11f0-b813-9de793e7cddf</guid><pubDate>Tue, 26 Aug 2025 15:56:37 GMT</pubDate></item><item><category></category><title>‘I will be displaced once again’: Gaza City residents forced to flee as military operation begins</title><link>https://www.france24.com/en/middle-east/20250822-gaza-city-residents-israel-military-operation-displaced</link><description>
As Israel announced its intention to seize Gaza City on August 20, amateur and satellite images from the previous days show intensified air strikes by the Israeli military, significant destruction, and the emptying of several displaced camps. Our Observers in the city prepare to face yet another displacement.
</description><media:thumbnail url="https://s.observers.france24.com/media/display/721ca3fa-8295-11f0-b29b-005056bfb2b6/w:1024/p:16x9/image4-65.png"/><enclosure url="https://s.observers.france24.com/media/display/721ca3fa-8295-11f0-b29b-005056bfb2b6/w:1024/p:16x9/image4-65.png" type="image/png" length="0"/><guid isPermaLink="false">80af9c6a-8295-11f0-9b88-1d47ae917c11</guid><pubDate>Tue, 26 Aug 2025 15:58:26 GMT</pubDate></item><item><category></category><title>Gunfire during aid distribution in Gaza: 'I never want to go back there'</title><link>https://www.france24.com/en/middle-east/20250725-gunfire-aid-distribution-israel-gaza-civilians-food-zikim-wfp</link><description>
The morning of July 20, a convoy of 25 trucks from the World Food Programme (WFP) carrying essential aid crossed the border into northern Gaza. Civilians who were gathering to try to access the aid came under fire by the Israeli military, according to both the WFP and those present. The Israeli army denies this. Our team spoke to Ahmed Abo Askar, a young Palestinian who was among those trying to collect food.
</description><media:thumbnail url="https://s.observers.france24.com/media/display/e17a01dc-6b9f-11f0-a4a5-005056bf30b7/w:1024/p:16x9/image1-117.png"/><enclosure url="https://s.observers.france24.com/media/display/e17a01dc-6b9f-11f0-a4a5-005056bf30b7/w:1024/p:16x9/image1-117.png" type="image/png" length="0"/><guid isPermaLink="false">ec1ae020-6b9f-11f0-ae6c-91f830f8538d</guid><pubDate>Mon, 28 Jul 2025 10:45:05 GMT</pubDate></item><item><category></category><title>Apologies by US CEO caught in Coldplay 'kiss cam' scandal were faked</title><link>https://www.france24.com/en/americas/20250723-apologies-fake-us-ceo-coldplay-concert-kiss-cam-byron-astronomer</link><description>
When he was caught on camera at a Coldplay concert with his arms wrapped around his alleged mistress, Andy Byron, the then CEO of the American company Astronomer, appeared to publish an apology online. It turns out that it was a fake statement published by a satirical account. 
</description><media:thumbnail url="https://s.observers.france24.com/media/display/6e0402a2-67c6-11f0-8890-005056a90284/w:1024/p:16x9/byron.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://s.observers.france24.com/media/display/6e0402a2-67c6-11f0-8890-005056a90284/w:1024/p:16x9/byron.jpg" type="image/jpeg" length="0"/><guid isPermaLink="false">75fe11dc-67c6-11f0-b9d3-d9e711f16243</guid><pubDate>Wed, 23 Jul 2025 13:10:52 GMT</pubDate></item><item><category>Debunked</category><title>That video said to show Trump selecting a young girl at an Epstein party? It’s AI</title><link>https://www.france24.com/en/americas/20250721-video-donald-trump-selecting-young-girl-epstein-maxwell-fake-artificial-intelligence</link><description>
Social media users have been sharing a video that reportedly shows Donald Trump selecting a young girl forced into prostitution. He appears alongside Ghislaine Maxwell, the longtime companion of Jeffrey Epstein, who died by suicide while facing charges of the sexual trafficking of minors. However, this video is not real – it was created by AI. 
</description><media:thumbnail url="https://s.observers.france24.com/media/display/202444e4-663f-11f0-9b69-005056a90284/w:1024/p:16x9/cover-epstein.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://s.observers.france24.com/media/display/202444e4-663f-11f0-9b69-005056a90284/w:1024/p:16x9/cover-epstein.jpg" type="image/jpeg" length="0"/><guid isPermaLink="false">31b54604-663f-11f0-ac5c-fb46652623eb</guid><pubDate>Mon, 21 Jul 2025 14:30:05 GMT</pubDate></item><item><category></category><title>Indigenous Indian village dismantled in the name of tiger protection</title><link>https://www.france24.com/en/asia-pacific/20250718-india-indigenous-village-dismantled-tiger-protection-nagarhole-reserve</link><description>
Police and park rangers in Nagarhole National Park in southwestern India tore down an Indigenous village on June 18. They claim that the presence of the Jenu Kuruba people is harmful to the park’s tigers, even though they worship tigers as part of their belief system. Several Jenu Kuruba families had moved back in May to land that their ancestors had been forcibly displaced from.
</description><media:thumbnail url="https://s.observers.france24.com/media/display/7101a924-6400-11f0-ac36-005056bfb2b6/w:1024/p:16x9/image3-97.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://s.observers.france24.com/media/display/7101a924-6400-11f0-ac36-005056bfb2b6/w:1024/p:16x9/image3-97.jpg" type="image/jpeg" length="0"/><guid isPermaLink="false">a3148f94-6400-11f0-a6db-0913ba27437d</guid><pubDate>Fri, 18 Jul 2025 17:57:14 GMT</pubDate></item><item><category></category><title>How influencers are getting clicks by sharing AI-generated, fake images of the Holocaust</title><link>https://www.france24.com/en/europe/20250717-influencers-clicks-sharing-ai-generated-fake-images-holocaust</link><description>
Social media influencers have been sharing an image of an emaciated man playing the violin. They say he was a violinist in the orchestra at the Auschwitz concentration camp who was forced to play during the final moments of prisoners sent to the gas chambers. But the image was AI-generated – and the story it tells does not align with the real history of the Auschwitz orchestra.
</description><media:thumbnail url="https://s.observers.france24.com/media/display/a0745754-6330-11f0-af9e-005056a97e36/w:1024/p:16x9/cover-heinek.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://s.observers.france24.com/media/display/a0745754-6330-11f0-af9e-005056a97e36/w:1024/p:16x9/cover-heinek.jpg" type="image/jpeg" length="0"/><guid isPermaLink="false">a4eca872-6330-11f0-b81d-17e97a9d2e54</guid><pubDate>Thu, 17 Jul 2025 17:08:22 GMT</pubDate></item><item><category></category><title>What we know about mysterious explosions on ships visiting Russian ports</title><link>https://www.france24.com/en/europe/20250715-what-we-know-mysterious-explosions-ships-russian-ports-calls</link><description>
Since January 2025, six tankers have been struck by unexplained explosions shortly after entering Russian ports. Many questions remain about the circumstances surrounding the blasts but several industry analysts believe sabotage, carried out by a state actor, is most likely responsible. 
</description><media:thumbnail url="https://s.observers.france24.com/media/display/4ae2ab08-621b-11f0-85f6-005056a90284/w:1024/p:16x9/cover-ok-1.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://s.observers.france24.com/media/display/4ae2ab08-621b-11f0-85f6-005056a90284/w:1024/p:16x9/cover-ok-1.jpg" type="image/jpeg" length="0"/><guid isPermaLink="false">4ecee240-621b-11f0-9ba7-511a3aa92aeb</guid><pubDate>Wed, 16 Jul 2025 08:03:07 GMT</pubDate></item><item><category></category><title>Guinea: Doumbouya's power leaves opponents mute with fear</title><link>https://www.france24.com/en/africa/20250711-guinea-mamady-doumbouya-power-leaves-opponents-mute-fear</link><description>
Opposition figures are disappearing in Guinea, and protests and media outlets have been banned. Four years after the coup, opponents of President Mamady Doumbouya are denouncing the general's stranglehold on Guinea. His supporters, on the other hand, praise the enthusiasm he is reportedly generating as crucial elections draw near. 
</description><media:thumbnail url="https://s.observers.france24.com/media/display/3d9943c0-6159-11f0-b591-005056a90284/w:1024/p:16x9/doumbouya-guinee-opposants.png"/><enclosure url="https://s.observers.france24.com/media/display/3d9943c0-6159-11f0-b591-005056a90284/w:1024/p:16x9/doumbouya-guinee-opposants.png" type="image/png" length="0"/><guid isPermaLink="false">41a3e966-6159-11f0-b662-6f9c429d3450</guid><pubDate>Tue, 15 Jul 2025 08:54:02 GMT</pubDate></item><item><category></category><title>Turkey attempts to neutralise PKK tunnels in Iraq despite dissolution of Kurdish militant group</title><link>https://www.france24.com/en/middle-east/20250710-turkey-neutralise-pkk-tunnels-iraq-dissolution-kurdish-militant-group</link><description>
While the PKK has announced its dissolution and intention to stop fighting, clashes continue in Iraqi Kurdistan between Kurdish guerrillas and the Turkish army. Turkish forces seek to neutralise the PKK's extensive tunnel network in the Gara Mountains – a war unfolding in a remote region, away from cameras.
</description><media:thumbnail url="https://s.observers.france24.com/media/display/5e8504bc-5e33-11f0-9e39-005056a90284/w:1024/p:16x9/image5-46.png"/><enclosure url="https://s.observers.france24.com/media/display/5e8504bc-5e33-11f0-9e39-005056a90284/w:1024/p:16x9/image5-46.png" type="image/png" length="0"/><guid isPermaLink="false">6a313fba-5e33-11f0-b92a-e92991739be9</guid><pubDate>Fri, 11 Jul 2025 08:45:36 GMT</pubDate></item><item><category></category><title>Drones: A new weapon for Colombia’s guerrillas</title><link>https://www.france24.com/en/americas/20250707-colombia-drones-armed-conflict-guerrillas-projectiles-human-rights-farc-eln</link><description>
Drone attacks in Colombia have been on the rise since 2024. Armed groups use drones to fire projectiles at security forces and rival groups. However, civilians are also being affected, and experts say that the authorities should have taken quicker action to manage the threat.
</description><media:thumbnail url="https://s.observers.france24.com/media/display/9388e7e0-5b4b-11f0-9bc2-005056a97e36/w:1024/p:16x9/colombie-fond-drones-1.png"/><enclosure url="https://s.observers.france24.com/media/display/9388e7e0-5b4b-11f0-9bc2-005056a97e36/w:1024/p:16x9/colombie-fond-drones-1.png" type="image/png" length="0"/><guid isPermaLink="false">ad0cc7e0-5b4b-11f0-8c5d-fb20c4ab4909</guid><pubDate>Mon, 07 Jul 2025 16:01:43 GMT</pubDate></item><item><category></category><title>Chinese media sphere wages smear campaign against France's Rafale jet</title><link>https://www.france24.com/en/asia-pacific/20250704-sinosphere-smear-campaign-french-rafale-fighter-jet</link><description>
The clashes between India and Pakistan on May 6 gave rise to a wave of anti-Rafale smears from China, following the news of the alleged destruction of at least one French fighter jet. An entire Chinese media and digital ecosystem was mobilised to attack the aircraft's reputation, employing humourous sketches, fake videos from video games and distorted information.
</description><media:thumbnail url="https://s.observers.france24.com/media/display/1a438a90-58e2-11f0-a026-005056bfb2b6/w:1024/p:16x9/image4-8-1.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://s.observers.france24.com/media/display/1a438a90-58e2-11f0-a026-005056bfb2b6/w:1024/p:16x9/image4-8-1.jpg" type="image/jpeg" length="0"/><guid isPermaLink="false">35c6a22a-58e2-11f0-96a6-39a756340b8c</guid><pubDate>Fri, 04 Jul 2025 14:21:43 GMT</pubDate></item><item><category></category><title>Gaza: In the rubble of a cafe bombed by Israel</title><link>https://www.france24.com/en/middle-east/20250703-gaza-al-baqa-cafe-israeli-air-strike</link><description>
On June 30, 2025, the Israeli army bombed the Al-Baqa cafe in Gaza City. The beachfront venue was a gathering spot for residents and journalists seeking Wi-Fi connection. 
</description><media:thumbnail url="https://s.observers.france24.com/media/display/51867146-58b2-11f0-8ecb-005056a97e36/w:1024/p:16x9/design-sans-titre-1-1.png"/><enclosure url="https://s.observers.france24.com/media/display/51867146-58b2-11f0-8ecb-005056a97e36/w:1024/p:16x9/design-sans-titre-1-1.png" type="image/png" length="0"/><guid isPermaLink="false">57b7a74c-58b2-11f0-9d7e-1d061e296f60</guid><pubDate>Fri, 04 Jul 2025 08:39:04 GMT</pubDate></item><item><category></category><title>West Bank: Israeli settlers continue to harass Palestinians, reportedly burn down house</title><link>https://www.france24.com/en/middle-east/20250702-west-bank-israeli-settlers-harass-palestinians-reportedly-burn-down-house-masafer-yatta</link><description>
On the night of June 24 to 25, a fire completely destroyed a Palestinian house. The local population blamed the fire on Israeli settlers from the nearby settlement, built on the site of Susya, a former Palestinian village.
</description><media:thumbnail url="https://s.observers.france24.com/media/display/39805046-575c-11f0-bbd8-005056bf30b7/w:1024/p:16x9/design-sans-titre.png"/><enclosure url="https://s.observers.france24.com/media/display/39805046-575c-11f0-bbd8-005056bf30b7/w:1024/p:16x9/design-sans-titre.png" type="image/png" length="0"/><guid isPermaLink="false">41181af0-575c-11f0-8320-7fd545766001</guid><pubDate>Wed, 02 Jul 2025 15:50:18 GMT</pubDate></item><item><category></category><title>'We only have one exit': Life under blockade in West Bank villages</title><link>https://www.france24.com/en/middle-east/20250628-west-bank-blockade-villages-israel-iron-gates-settlements</link><description>
Since the Israel-Iran war started in June 2025, life has become even more constrained in Ras Karkar, a village west of Ramallah in the West Bank. Hatem Nofal, head of the local emergency committee, describes a daily existence dictated by Israeli iron gates, expanding settlements, and the increasing isolation of his community.
</description><media:thumbnail url="https://s.observers.france24.com/media/display/19eed116-5415-11f0-a341-005056bfb2b6/w:1024/p:16x9/teaser-cijordanie.png"/><enclosure url="https://s.observers.france24.com/media/display/19eed116-5415-11f0-a341-005056bfb2b6/w:1024/p:16x9/teaser-cijordanie.png" type="image/png" length="0"/><guid isPermaLink="false">ec934dd4-5589-11f0-b459-51ea6118c981</guid><pubDate>Mon, 30 Jun 2025 08:12:11 GMT</pubDate></item><item><category></category><title>Iran arrests 700 'Israeli agents', but where are the weapons?</title><link>https://www.france24.com/en/middle-east/20250627-iran-arrests-seized-weapons-mossad-connection-israel</link><description>
Iranian state media announced on Wednesday that Iran’s security forces have arrested more than 700 people on suspicion of belonging to an "Israeli spy network" since Israel’s June 13 attack.
</description><media:thumbnail url="https://s.observers.france24.com/media/display/70f36e4a-537a-11f0-bade-005056a97e36/w:1024/p:16x9/Capture-d-e%CC%81cran-2025-06-27-a%CC%80-19-15-45.png"/><enclosure url="https://s.observers.france24.com/media/display/70f36e4a-537a-11f0-bade-005056a97e36/w:1024/p:16x9/Capture-d-e%CC%81cran-2025-06-27-a%CC%80-19-15-45.png" type="image/png" length="0"/><guid isPermaLink="false">78337ae2-537a-11f0-91ef-51dd5f3a3549</guid><pubDate>Fri, 27 Jun 2025 17:17:04 GMT</pubDate></item><item><category></category><title>Community members confront immigration raids in ‘Mexican Beverly Hills’</title><link>https://www.france24.com/en/americas/20250626-united-states-community-members-confront-immigration-raids-ice-downey</link><description>
Downey, California, was rocked on June 11 by a series of Immigration and Customs Enforcement (ICE) raids targeting local businesses, resulting in multiple arrests. A community member who intervened in one incident, leading to the release of a man, told the FRANCE 24 Observers team that the community is shaken but united.
</description><media:thumbnail url="https://s.observers.france24.com/media/display/e102cde6-5296-11f0-9e8f-005056a90284/w:1024/p:16x9/downey-ice-arrest.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://s.observers.france24.com/media/display/e102cde6-5296-11f0-9e8f-005056a90284/w:1024/p:16x9/downey-ice-arrest.jpg" type="image/jpeg" length="0"/><guid isPermaLink="false">e5684212-5296-11f0-a7a5-eda73ebf6c34</guid><pubDate>Thu, 26 Jun 2025 14:07:29 GMT</pubDate></item><item><category>Debunked</category><title>Did a ‘Harvard report’ reveal 377,000 Gazans are ‘missing’? The number has been misinterpreted</title><link>https://www.france24.com/en/middle-east/20250625-harvard-report-gaza-missing-misinterpreted-number-israel</link><description>
Are 377,000 people “missing” in Gaza? This number has been shared by many internet users and media, who claim to be relying on a “Harvard report”. However, this figure misinterprets an Israeli study, which itself contains an error in the numbers at the root of the confusion. As of June 24, 56,077 Gazans have been killed since October 7, 2023, according to the health ministry in Hamas-run Gaza.
</description><media:thumbnail url="https://s.observers.france24.com/media/display/0e6ea722-526b-11f0-84e2-005056a97e36/w:1024/p:16x9/Design-sans-titre-43.jpg"/><enclosure url="https://s.observers.france24.com/media/display/0e6ea722-526b-11f0-84e2-005056a97e36/w:1024/p:16x9/Design-sans-titre-43.jpg" type="image/jpeg" length="0"/><guid isPermaLink="false">168bfe6e-526b-11f0-a062-2bf94e97973c</guid><pubDate>Thu, 26 Jun 2025 08:53:54 GMT</pubDate></item><item><category></category><title>Israel: Arab-Israelis face unequal access to bomb shelters</title><link>https://www.france24.com/en/middle-east/20250624-arab-israelis-unequal-access-bomb-shelters-iran-missile-attacks</link><description>
As the ceasefire between Israel and Iran remains fragile, there has been a growing number of reports in recent days of people in Israel being denied access to bomb shelters, particularly Arab-Israeli citizens.
</description><media:thumbnail url="https://s.observers.france24.com/media/display/718264b2-519d-11f0-b65a-005056bfb2b6/w:1024/p:16x9/Design-sans-titre-5.png"/><enclosure url="https://s.observers.france24.com/media/display/718264b2-519d-11f0-b65a-005056bfb2b6/w:1024/p:16x9/Design-sans-titre-5.png" type="image/png" length="0"/><guid isPermaLink="false">7aa7bbaa-519d-11f0-9ca6-1303e9e7747a</guid><pubDate>Wed, 25 Jun 2025 08:22:05 GMT</pubDate></item><item><category>DEBUNKED</category><title>No definite proof for Iran’s claims it shot down Israeli F-35 fighter jets</title><link>https://www.france24.com/en/middle-east/20250624-iran-shot-down-israel-f-35-fighter-jets-no-definite-proof</link><description>
Since the start of the war between Israel and Iran, a number of Iranian media outlets with close links to the government have reported that Iran had shot down four Israeli F-35 fighter jets. However, for the time being, there is no proof to support these claims and military experts consider them unlikely.
</description><media:thumbnail url="https://s.observers.france24.com/media/display/f6620a82-519a-11f0-ad6a-005056a97e36/w:1024/p:16x9/Design-sans-titre-42-1.png"/><enclosure url="https://s.observers.france24.com/media/display/f6620a82-519a-11f0-ad6a-005056a97e36/w:1024/p:16x9/Design-sans-titre-42-1.png" type="image/png" length="0"/><guid isPermaLink="false">0d21557a-519b-11f0-a0ed-1303e9e7747a</guid><pubDate>Wed, 25 Jun 2025 08:04:43 GMT</pubDate></item></channel></rss>
